Arsenal playmaker, Mesut Ozil has expressed disappointment after Mikel Arteta’s men failed to beat Crystal Palace in the Premier League on Saturday. Arsenal played a 1-1 draw with Crystal Palace at Selhurst Park, thanks to Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang’s first half goal. Jordan Ayew scored the equaliser in the 54 minute of the encounter for Roy Hodgson’s men. Reacting to the result, Ozil took to his official Twitter page after the match and wrote: “Slightly disappointed with the final score. “We were fighting all together to get the away win, but it wasn’t meant to be. “Let’s stay positive and keep believing, Gunners.” Arsenal’s next Premier League fixture is against Sheffield United on January 18.